<cite><a href="http://www.budsas.org/ebud/dict-pe/" target="_blank" title="goto glossary/dictionary page">Source</a>: <span>BuddhaSasana: Concise Pali-English Dictionary</span></cite><p>sumati : <em>(m.) </em>a wise man.</p><section class="suffix split"><img src="/uploads/a/Pali-tall.jpg" class="context" alt="Pali book cover"><header><em>context information</em></header><p>Pali is the language of the Tipiṭaka, which is the sacred canon of Theravāda Buddhism and contains much of the Buddha’s speech. Closeley related to Sanskrit, both languages are used interchangeably between religions.</p>
<div class="spacer"></div><footer><p>Discover the meaning of <em>sumati</em> in the context of Pali from relevant books on <a href="http://www.exoticindiaart.com/book/Buddhist/aff11436/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Exotic India <i class="fas fa-external-link-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></p></footer></section><h3 id="sanskrit">Sanskrit dictionary</h3> 
<div class="row justify-content-between cat-toolbar">

<div class="col-12 col-md-auto" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/DefinedTermSet">
<small>
